  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lilongwe Diocese HBC</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lilongwe Diocese Home Based Care programme envisions itself has  been contributing to the reduction of the impact of HIV and AIDS in communities in Malawi by harnessing the people&#x2019;s potential through mobilising sustainable community responses to prevent the spread and mitigate the impact of HIV and AIDS to affected and infected individuals including children and their families.
In order to realise their vision they network with other NGOs and Faith Based Organisations.
The major activities of the Diocese will be HIV and AIDS prevention and Management of HIV and AIDS. The prevalent practices to be tackled in part in the process are as follows:
- Sexual cultural practices such as initiation, rituals associated with death of spouse or other practices that end up exposing young girls &#x2018; being blankets for chiefs&#x2019;
- Trading of sex for money
- Addressing inconsistent and inaccurate messages relating to the promotion of condoms
- Addressing stigma and discrimination which continue to suppress openness about HIV and AIDS
- Inadequate legal enforcements in controlling sexual exploitation of girls and boys in resort parts o Malawi and many other recreational facilities.
- Establishing an effective referral system
- Ensuring and facilitating accessibility of facilities to clients and communities , for example , PMTCT, ART
- Provision of basic nursing care of chronically ill in their homes and alleviation of pain.
- Following up patients on treatment and adherence
- Formation of support groups.</narrative>
  </description>
